There is some variation in the size of tergal tomentum spots and bands. In the females, T2 lateral fascia (
Fig. 11
) is often reduced to two lateral spots (
Fig. 9
), and two lateral spots on T3 and T4 are reduced to one small spot (
Fig. 9
). Among the male specimens we have not found any reduction of the T2 lateral fascia, but lateral fasciae on T3 and T4 are usually reduced to just spots and only a few specimens have complete lateral fasciae on these terga.

Distribution. Russia (* Irkutsk Provinse, Buryatia , *Zabaikalskiy Terr.,* Khabarovsk Prov. , *JewishAutonomous Prov., * Amur Prov. , Primorskiy Terr.), Mongolia , * China ( Inner Mongolia ), Japan ( Hokkaido , Honshu, Shikoku, Kyushu, Ryukyu) ( Hirashima & Tadauchi 1979 ; Romankova 1995 ; Proshchalykin & Kupianskaya 2009 ;
Levchenko et al . 2017
; Astafurova & Proshchalykin 2021 ).
